of his own making in the s and ’s alexandre reza was the man harry winston cartier and boucheron turned to when a client requested a particularly rare piecephotograph courtesy of alexandre reza via town  country though the boutique was closed in  reza’s son olivier has brilliantly revived his father’s business by offering his contemporary designs alongside his father’s archival pieces both of which will be featured in sotheby’s exhibition  together the pieces in the exhibition are a mesmerizing peek into reza’s splendid vaults which are rumored to house one of the world’s largest and most impressive private collections of gemstones and jewels alexandre reza by vivienne beckerphoto courtesy of assouline david bennett chairman of sotheby’s jewelry division europe  middle east comments “alexandre reza’s legacy forms an integral and important part of the history of post war jewelry sotheby’s is honored to showcase his work through this special exhibition which will include many of the most important jewels and parures created by alexandre reza during the last  years featuring spectacular diamonds natural pearls and superb colored gems we are particularly thrilled to support his son olivier as he carries the reza name to the next generation of collectors and connoisseurs with his exciting new designs” photo courtesy of alexandre reza via sotheby’s highlights of the exhibition include several of reza’s iconic parures set with impressivelysized emeralds and sapphires the remarkable “notre dame” clip featuring a carat unheated ceylon sapphire and a magnificent ring with a carat burmese sapphire flanked by a double bombé mounting swathed with diamonds in  the exhibition will travel to sotheby’s offices around the world including beijing doha and london gold natural pearl and diamond “le carcan” necklace alexandre reza gold natural pearl and diamond “le carcan” necklace alexandre rezaphoto courtesy of sotheby’s historicallyinspired gold necklace set with  variously cut diamon